wiki_section_title: Wooden roller coasters

wiki_section_text: 

intro: Curtis D. Summers (September 17, 1929 - May 11, 1992) was an engineer and American roller coaster designer credited for designing or providing structural engineering on 25 wooden roller coasters around the world. He earned a degree in Architectural Engineering from Kansas State University and was a registered engineer in 40 states.
